- City  

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Courses
- CourseID (Primary Key)  
- CourseName  
- Duration  

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Enrollments
- EnrollmentID (Primary Key)  
- StudentID (Foreign Key)  
- CourseID (Foreign Key)  
- EnrollmentDate  

---
## Database & Table Creation
- Created database `StudentsDB`
- Designed relational tables
- Defined primary and foreign keys

##Insert Sample Data
Inserted sample records into:
- Students
- Courses
- Enrollments

## INNER JOIN
Fetched students along with their enrolled courses.

## LEFT JOIN & RIGHT JOIN
- LEFT JOIN ‚Üí Show all students (including those without enrollments)
- RIGHT JOIN ‚Üí Show all courses (including those without enrollments)

## Numeric Functions
Used:
- ROUND()
- ABS()
- MOD()

## String Functions (Part 1)
Used:
- CONCAT()
- LENGTH()

##String Functions (Part 2)
Used:
- REPLACE()
- SUBSTRING()

## Case Conversion
Used:
- UPPER()
- LOWER()

##Date Functions
Used:
- NOW()
- DATEDIFF()
- DATE_ADD()

## Combined Enrollment Report
Built a report displaying:
- Student ID
- Enrollment ID
- Current Date & Time
- Days Difference
- Follow-up Date

